<h2>Saving a Website</h2>

<p>Saving a website is simple. After making an account, you'll be presented with a blank screen with a bar that says "Enter Website".</p>

<div class="sample1" style="background-image: url(http://i.imgur.com/jTqJ7BP.png)"></div>

<p><em>Welcome!</em></p>

<p>You copy and paste a url into the bar, press Enter, and voila, you have a brand new bookmark.</p>

<div class="sample1" style="background-image: url(http://i.imgur.com/qVsoDWD.png
)"></div>

<p><em>Congrats on the new bookmark!</em></p>

<p>Go ahead and save a couple of bookmarks. You'll be glad you did.</p><p><p>
<h2>Searching Bookmarks</h2>
<p>After having so many bookmarks, you'd think finding them would be a drag.</p>

<div class="sample1" style="background-image: url(http://i.imgur.com/3X2NXNQ.png
)"></div>

<p><em>I know I have Google in here somewhere...</em></p>

<p>But all you have to do is search for it in the search bar. You can search the exact title, or you can search keywords of the website.</p>

<div class="sample1" style="background-image: url(http://i.imgur.com/EL3N4TU.png)"></div>

<p><em>I found Google AND a useless search engine!</em></p>

<p>You can even search through public bookmarks if you'd like to see what else people have been saving.</p>

